content.description: Stand start with low left hand in the crack, a high right hand on a sloper crimp on the lip, and obvious feet at the bottom. Work your hands up the edges and gain a small foot on the face. Throw a heel and press for a good top out. The detached block out left is off for this climb.Nice flat landing and beautiful climb or warmup. There is a possible sit start with low feet and hands on the lower right crimp rail that may add a couple grades.Â Enjoy the climb and the multitude of chipmunk friends you'll find at this boulder!
content.location: Find the Cross Overhang, walk under the boulder and take a left at the tree to go slightly uphill. This is the first boulder on your right - right next to the Cross Overhang down climb.

content.description: Beautiful boulder with large crack on the left. Good feet, sloper crimps, and fun top out.
